The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the Saint Francis de Sales School in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. He praised Pennsylvania for leading the way in providing educational opportunities through school choice. Pence emphasized the importance of every child having access to a quality education, regardless of background or zip code. He mentioned the Education Freedom Scholarships program, which aims to give 1 million more students the freedom to attend the school of their choice. Pence also highlighted the success stories of families who have benefited from school choice scholarships. He encouraged the audience to support and advocate for school choice, despite resistance from special interests and politicians. Pence concluded by urging the students to seize the opportunity they have been given and to work hard to achieve their dreams.